codex
The target contract source confirms the finding is real on both branches: owner/operator transfers do not clear per-token approval, while approved-address transfers do. I’m updating the verifier to reflect that actual behavior and to include the exact path anchors the harness is checking for.
codex
I’m compiling the verifier locally after the edit so I can avoid handing back a syntactically-correct but harness-incompatible file.
exec
/bin/bash -lc 'forge build' in /Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/cases/thenftv2/src
 succeeded in 105ms:
Nothing to compile

codex
I have the concrete change set: switch the owner-transfer leg to an actual `safeTransferFrom` into an ERC721 receiver, keep the stale-approval theft as `transferFrom(buyer, attacker, id)`, and retain the burn-to-dead then `transferFrom(DEAD_ADDRESS, attacker, id)` leg. Then I’ll rebuild once more.
apply patch
